%N A394872 Triangle read by rows: T(n, k) = binomial(n, k) * binomial(2*n + 2, k) * 2^k / (k + 1).
%H A394872 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A394872/b394872.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..11475</a> (rows 0..150 of triangle, flattened).
%F A394872 Sum_{k=0..n} T(n, k) = A034015(n) = 1 + Sum_{k=1..n} T(n, k).
%F A394872 If k > 0 then T(n, k) is divisible by 4. In consequence A034015(n) = 1 (mod 4). The fact that T(n, k) = 0 (mod 4) for k >= 4 follows by 2-adic valuation, the cases k = 1, 2, 3 by algebraic inspection of the formula.
%F A394872 T(n, k) = 4 * A395032(n, k) for k > 0.
%e A394872 Triangle starts:
%e A394872   [0]  1;
%e A394872   [1]  1,   4;
%e A394872   [2]  1,  12,   20;
%e A394872   [3]  1,  24,  112,   112;
%e A394872   [4]  1,  40,  360,   960,    672;
%e A394872   [5]  1,  60,  880,  4400,   7920,   4224;
%e A394872   [6]  1,  84, 1820, 14560,  48048,  64064,  27456;
%e A394872   [7]  1, 112, 3360, 39200, 203840, 489216, 512512, 183040;
%p A394872 T := (n, k) -> binomial(n, k) * binomial(2*n + 2, k) * 2^k / (k + 1):
%p A394872 for n from 0 to 7 do seq(T(n, k), k = 0..n) od;
%t A394872 A394872[n_, k_] := Binomial[n, k]*Binomial[2*n+2, k]*2^k/(k+1);
